com.madisp.stupid.context

Class StackContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.madisp.stupid.context.BaseContext
      • com.madisp.stupid.context.StackContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExecContext

    public class StackContext
extends BaseContext
    StackContext is a LIFO-stack container of ExecContext instances. StackContext tries to forward the methods to the underlying context by starting from the most recently added one. If a NoSuch* exception is thrown (e.g. no field) then the next ExecContext is tried and so on. This enables one to mix-and-match various context in a fairly predictible manner. Some neat tricks: Add a VarContext with the type CREATE_ON_SET_OR_GET before adding another context on top. This will allow stupid scripts to define their own variables while still enabling access to some other context, a ReflectionContext to access a Java API for instance. The push/pop is used by a Block to set the block arguments when yielding.
